#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/compound_interest_calculator.html:314
msgid "Understanding Compound Interest"
msgstr "Memahami Faedah Kompaun"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/compound_interest_calculator.html:317
msgid "The Power of Compounding"
msgstr "Kuasa Pengkompaunan"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/compound_interest_calculator.html:318
msgid ""
"Compound interest is often called the eighth wonder of the world. Unlike "
"simple interest, compound interest earns interest on your interest, leading "
"to exponential growth over time."
msgstr ""
"Faedah kompaun sering dipanggil keajaiban dunia kelapan. Tidak seperti "
"faedah mudah, faedah kompaun memperoleh faedah ke atas minat anda, yang "
"membawa kepada pertumbuhan eksponen dari semasa ke semasa."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/compound_interest_calculator.html:320
msgid "Compound Frequency Matters"
msgstr "Perkara Frekuensi Kompaun"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/compound_interest_calculator.html:321
msgid ""
"The more frequently interest compounds, the more you earn. Daily compounding"
" earns more than monthly, which earns more than annually. However, the "
"differences are usually small."
msgstr ""
"Lebih kerap kompaun faedah, lebih banyak pendapatan anda. Pengkompaunan "
"harian memperoleh lebih daripada bulanan, yang memperoleh lebih daripada "
"setiap tahun. Walau bagaimanapun, perbezaan biasanya kecil."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/compound_interest_calculator.html:324
msgid "Time Is Your Greatest Asset"
msgstr "Masa Adalah Aset Terhebat Anda"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/compound_interest_calculator.html:325
msgid ""
"The longer your money compounds, the more dramatic the growth. Starting "
"early, even with smaller amounts, often beats starting later with larger "
"amounts."
msgstr ""
"Semakin lama wang anda berkumpul, semakin dramatik pertumbuhannya. Bermula "
"awal, walaupun dengan jumlah yang lebih kecil, selalunya berdegup bermula "
"kemudian dengan jumlah yang lebih besar."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/compound_interest_calculator.html:327
msgid "The Rule of 72"
msgstr "Peraturan 72"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/compound_interest_calculator.html:328
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Divide 72 by your interest rate to estimate how many years it takes to "
"double your money. At 7%% interest, your money doubles approximately every "
"10 years."
msgstr ""
"Bahagikan 72 dengan kadar faedah anda untuk menganggarkan berapa tahun yang "
"diperlukan untuk menggandakan wang anda. Dengan faedah 7%%, wang anda "
"berganda kira-kira setiap 10 tahun."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/compound_interest_calculator.html:339
msgid "What is the difference between simple and compound interest?"
msgstr "Apakah perbezaan antara faedah mudah dan kompaun?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/compound_interest_calculator.html:345
msgid ""
"Simple interest is calculated only on the original principal. Compound "
"interest is calculated on the principal plus any accumulated interest, "
"leading to faster growth over time."
msgstr ""
"Faedah mudah dikira hanya pada prinsipal asal. Faedah kompaun dikira pada "
"prinsipal ditambah sebarang faedah terkumpul, yang membawa kepada "
"pertumbuhan yang lebih pantas dari semasa ke semasa."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/compound_interest_calculator.html:351
msgid "How does compound frequency affect my returns?"
msgstr "Bagaimanakah kekerapan kompaun mempengaruhi pulangan saya?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/compound_interest_calculator.html:357
msgid ""
"More frequent compounding means your interest starts earning interest "
"sooner, resulting in higher total returns. However, the difference between "
"daily and monthly compounding is often minimal."
msgstr ""
"Pengkompaunan yang lebih kerap bermakna minat anda mula memperoleh faedah "
"lebih awal, menghasilkan jumlah pulangan yang lebih tinggi. Walau "
"bagaimanapun, perbezaan antara kompaun harian dan bulanan selalunya minimum."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/compound_interest_calculator.html:363
msgid "What is a realistic interest rate to use?"
msgstr "Apakah kadar faedah yang realistik untuk digunakan?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/compound_interest_calculator.html:369
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Savings accounts typically offer 0.5-5%%. Bonds may return 2-6%%. Stock "
"market has historically returned around 7-10%% annually (inflation-"
"adjusted). Use rates appropriate for your investment type."
msgstr ""
"Akaun simpanan biasanya menawarkan 0.5-5%%. Bon mungkin pulangan 2-6%%. "
"Pasaran saham secara sejarah telah kembali sekitar 7-10%% setiap tahun "
"(dilaraskan inflasi). Gunakan kadar yang sesuai untuk jenis pelaburan anda."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/compound_interest_calculator.html:375
msgid "Should I contribute at the beginning or end of the period?"
msgstr "Perlukah saya menyumbang pada awal atau akhir tempoh?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/compound_interest_calculator.html:381
msgid ""
"Contributing at the beginning of each period results in slightly higher "
"returns because your money has more time to compound. This is often called "
"'annuity due' vs 'ordinary annuity'."
msgstr ""
"Mencarum pada permulaan setiap tempoh menghasilkan pulangan yang lebih "
"tinggi sedikit kerana wang anda mempunyai lebih banyak masa untuk dikompaun."
" Ini sering dipanggil 'anuiti kena dibayar' vs 'annuiti biasa'."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/compound_interest_calculator.html:389
msgid "Investment Tips"
msgstr "Tips Pelaburan"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/compound_interest_calculator.html:395
msgid "Start investing as early as possible - time is your biggest advantage."
msgstr ""
"Mulakan pelaburan seawal mungkin - masa adalah kelebihan terbesar anda."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/compound_interest_calculator.html:401
msgid ""
"Consistent small contributions can outperform large one-time investments."
msgstr ""
"Sumbangan kecil yang konsisten boleh mengatasi prestasi pelaburan sekali "
"sahaja yang besar."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/compound_interest_calculator.html:407
msgid "Reinvest your dividends and interest to maximize compounding."
msgstr ""
"Labur semula dividen dan faedah anda untuk memaksimumkan pengkompaunan."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/compound_interest_calculator.html:413
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Keep fees low - even 1%% in fees can significantly reduce long-term returns."
msgstr ""
"Pastikan yuran rendah - walaupun 1%% dalam yuran boleh mengurangkan pulangan"
" jangka panjang dengan ketara."

